result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) and OWI (5th or 6th). The defendant was found guilty of Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) and the other charge, OWI (5th or 6th) was dismissed by the court.

  • Gary Robert Fleischman was found guilty of Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Court calls 14CF250 & 16CF227 @ 3:46 pm. Defendant Gary Robert Fleischman in court with attorney Tina M Abernethy-Mays.  Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State gives plea agreement, 14CF250 Dismissed and consolidated Ct 1, Ct 2 plea to charge, 16CF227 Plea to charge, Needs to waives p.h. 14CF250 impose and stay 5 yrs prison,  2 years prison and 3 years extended supervision, 1000 fine plus costs, DNA surcharge, AODA and follow through Absolute Sobriety &  No presence in establishments with Class B liquor license, 6 months jail, 3 years revocation, 3 years IID and Counseling deemed by agent. 16CF227 withheld sentence 3 years, costs, DNA Surcharge, AODA, Absolute Sobriety &  No presence in establishments with Class B liquor license and Counseling deemed by agent.  OWI 6th offense.  Atty Abernethy-Mays and def. agree with plea agreement.  16CF227   Defendant waives right to preliminary hearing.  Court accepts waiver and finds probable cause and binds over. Def. understands charges and penalties. 14CF250 PAC 6th offense, no contest, 16CF227 Bailjumping, no contest.  Dismissed and consolidated ct 1 in 14CF250.  Def. advised of constitutional rights & J.T. rights.  Def. understand elements.  Def. admits prior convictions. Atty Abernethy-Mays is satisfied.  Court finds pleas are freely & voluntarily given.  Factual basis stipulated.  Court finds factual basis, accepts plea and finds def. Guilty to Bailjumping in 16CF227 and PAC 6th offense in 14CF250. State gives sentencing recommendation. BAC. .069.  Atty Abernethy-Mays gives sentencing recommendation. Def. has nothing to say.  Court orders on 
14CF250 Court orders on ct 2  impose and stay sentence 5 yrs prison, 2 years initial confinement and 3 years extended supervision, stay 3 years probation, 1000 fine plus costs, Bond of $2500 applied to this case that posted in 16CF227 and 800 bond applied 1st and than bond from 16CF227, DNA Sample, $250 DNA surcharge, AODA and complete driver safety plan, 3 years revocation, retroactive to Admin Susp, 3 years IID, upon application,  Absolute Sobriety,  Counseling deemed by agent. No presence in establishments with Class B liquor license, 6 months jail, Def. makes statement on when to commence jail. Huber privileges, C. 5-3-17 @ 7 pm. 
16CF227 withheld sentence 3 years, concurrent to Ct 2 in 14CF250,  Same conditions that ordered on 14CF250, costs, $250 DNA Surcharge, AODA and follow through, Absolute Sobriety &  No presence in establishments with Class B liquor license and Counseling deemed by agent. Bond in this case to be applied to this case and balance to 14CF250 and if any bond left over will be returned to poster. Def. advised of firearm and voting rights.  Def. is eligible for substance abuse and not eligible for challenge program. State heard on credit, 14CF250 3 days credit and 16CF227 1 day credit.  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.
